ESCX-to delet the unwanted character
ESCU-to undo the last the command and U to undo the whole line
CTRL-R to redo
A-to append text at the end
:wq-to save and exit
:ql-to trash all changes
dw-move the cursor to the begining of the word to delete that word
2w-to move the cursor two words backward
3e-to move the cursor to the end of the third word forward
0(zero)-to move to the start of the line
d2w-which delet towards number can be  changed for deleting the number of consective words like d3w
dd- to delet the line and to add to delet to line number can be changed for deleting the number of consective words


$(to the end of line),etc
P-puts the previously deleted text after the cursor(type dd to delet the line and store it in a vim register and p to put the line
%-to find a matching).)or )
G-to move you to the bottom of the file
/-backward search n to find the next occurrence and N to search in opposite direction
?-forward search
:W-TEST(where test is file name you chose.).save the file
:r-filename will insert the content into the current file
R-to replace from one the charcter
YW-(copy)yanks one word
O-opens a line above the cursor
o-opens the line below the cursor and start insert mode
a-inserts text after the cursor
A-inserts text after the end of the line
e-command moves to the end of a word
y-operater yanks(copies)text,p puts(pastes)it
R-enters replace mode until<ESC>is pressed
CTRL-w to jump from one window to another
:s/old/new/g to substitute NEW for OLD where g is globally
gg-to move you to the start of the file
ce-delet the word and places you in insert mode
 
